---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Alert from '../../components/Alert.astro';
import Accordion from '../../components/Accordion.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Troubleshooting: Internet Slowdown After Filtering"
  description="Fix internet speed issues caused by content filtering. Learn how to identify bottlenecks and optimize DNS filtering performance."
>
  <Breadcrumb />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="relative pb-6 border-b-4 border-blue-600 dark:border-blue-500 mb-8">
      <div
        class="inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mb-4 bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900 text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-100"
      >
        Intermediate
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 leading-tight">
        Internet Slowdown After Filtering
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Your connection feels sluggish after implementing filtering. Let's identify and fix performance bottlenecks.
      </p>
      <div class="flex gap-6 flex-wrap text-base text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        <span>‚è±Ô∏è Time Required: 15-30 minutes</span>
        <span>üîß Difficulty: Intermediate</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <Alert type="info">
      <strong>Reality Check:</strong> Properly configured DNS filtering adds only 1-5ms latency (imperceptible). If you're
      experiencing significant slowdowns, something else is wrong.
    </Alert>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">First: Baseline Your Speed</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Before troubleshooting, measure your actual speeds:
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-4">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl"
            >1</span
          > Run Speed Tests
        </h3>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Temporarily disable filtering (change DNS back to automatic)</li>
          <li>Visit <strong>fast.com</strong> or <strong>speedtest.net</strong></li>
          <li>Record: Download, Upload, Ping/Latency</li>
          <li>Re-enable filtering (restore DNS settings)</li>
          <li>Run the same test again</li>
          <li>Compare results</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 my-4 rounded">
          <strong class="block text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 mb-2">What's Normal:</strong>
          <ul class="ml-4 mb-0 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>Ping increase:</strong> 1-5ms is normal, 10-20ms is acceptable</li>
            <li><strong>Download/Upload:</strong> Should see no change (0-2% variation)</li>
            <li><strong>Red flag:</strong> Ping increase &gt;50ms or speed drop &gt;10%</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-4">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl"
            >2</span
          > Identify the Cause
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Most slowdowns have nothing to do with filtering. Common culprits:
        </p>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">
          Network Congestion (Not Filtering)
        </h4>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Too many devices connected simultaneously</li>
          <li>Someone streaming 4K video or gaming</li>
          <li>Background updates/backups running</li>
          <li><strong>Test:</strong> Disconnect other devices. Speed improve? Not filtering's fault.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">ISP Issues (Not Filtering)</h4>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>ISP-side congestion during peak hours</li>
          <li>Service outages or degradation</li>
          <li>Oversubscribed neighborhood network</li>
          <li><strong>Test:</strong> Disable filtering. Still slow? Call ISP.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">
          Router Problems (Not Filtering)
        </h4>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Old router can't handle your internet speed</li>
          <li>Router overheating or failing</li>
          <li>Outdated firmware with bugs</li>
          <li><strong>Test:</strong> Connect computer directly to modem with Ethernet. Faster? Router issue.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Actual Filtering Issues (Rare)</h4>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Distant DNS server location</li>
          <li>DNS server overloaded/having issues</li>
          <li>Too many DNS lookups (misconfiguration)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Solutions by Cause</h2>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">If It's Actually DNS Filtering:</h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Switch to Faster DNS Servers</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Different providers have different server locations:
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
          <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900">
              <tr>
                <th
                  class="p-3 text-left border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 font-semibold text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100"
                  >Provider</th
                >
                <th
                  class="p-3 text-left border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 font-semibold text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100"
                  >Avg Latency</th
                >
                <th
                  class="p-3 text-left border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 font-semibold text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100"
                  >Server Locations</th
                >
                <th
                  class="p-3 text-left border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 font-semibold text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100"
                  >Status</th
                >
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-700">
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
                  >Cloudflare Family</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">12ms</td>
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
                  >275+ cities worldwide</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Fastest</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-700">
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
                  >CleanBrowsing</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">18ms</td>
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
                  >Global anycast network</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Fast</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-700">
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">OpenDNS</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">22ms</td>
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
                  >25+ data centers</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Good</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-700">
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
                  >Quad9 Family</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">25ms</td>
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
                  >150+ locations</td
                >
                <td class="p-3 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Good</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <Alert type="info">
          Try switching to <strong>Cloudflare for Families (1.1.1.3 / 1.0.0.3)</strong> for maximum speed with filtering.
        </Alert>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Use DNS Caching</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Reduce repeated lookups by enabling DNS caching on your router:
        </p>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Log into router admin panel</li>
          <li>Look for "DNS Proxy" or "DNS Caching" option</li>
          <li>Enable it if available</li>
          <li>Set cache time to 3600 seconds (1 hour)</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Optimize DNS Configuration</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Use only 2 DNS servers (primary + secondary), not 3-4</li>
          <li>Choose servers from same provider (don't mix OpenDNS + CleanBrowsing)</li>
          <li>Test individual servers and use the fastest one as primary</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Test Server Latency</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Find which DNS server is fastest from your location:
        </p>
        <pre
          class="bg-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-950 text-green-300 p-4 rounded overflow-x-auto my-4"><code>ping 208.67.222.123
ping 185.228.168.168
ping 1.1.1.3</code></pre>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Use the one with lowest ping time as your primary DNS.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">If It's Router-Related:</h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Update Router Firmware</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Log into router admin</li>
          <li>Navigate to System or Administration</li>
          <li>Check for firmware updates</li>
          <li>Update if available (improves performance + security)</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Restart Router Properly</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Unplug router AND modem from power</li>
          <li>Wait 30 seconds</li>
          <li>Plug in modem, wait for all lights to stabilize (2 min)</li>
          <li>Plug in router, wait for all lights to stabilize (2 min)</li>
          <li>Test speeds again</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Check Router Resources</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Some routers show resource usage:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>CPU usage &gt;80%? Too many devices or old router</li>
          <li>Memory &gt;90%? Reboot router or upgrade</li>
          <li>Check temperature - overheating causes slowdowns</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Upgrade Router (If Necessary)</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Signs you need a new router:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Router is 5+ years old</li>
          <li>Your internet speed exceeds router's rated speed</li>
          <li>You have 15+ connected devices</li>
          <li>Router doesn't support AC or AX WiFi standards</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Recommended: <strong>$80-150 router</strong> with AC1900+ or AX1800+ for most homes. See our <a
            href="/guides/router-config"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 underline"
            >router recommendations</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">If It's Software Filtering (Not DNS):</h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">
          Filtering Software Can Impact Performance
        </h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Software like Qustodio, Net Nanny, Bark runs on each device:
        </p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Uses 1-5% CPU constantly</li>
          <li>Can slow older devices significantly</li>
          <li>May conflict with other security software</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Optimization Steps:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Update software:</strong> Newer versions are more efficient</li>
          <li><strong>Reduce monitoring frequency:</strong> Check settings for "scan interval"</li>
          <li><strong>Exclude trusted sites:</strong> Add known-safe sites to whitelist</li>
          <li><strong>Uninstall conflicting software:</strong> Don't run multiple antivirus/filtering apps</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Consider Hybrid Approach:</h4>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">Reduce software filtering load:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Use DNS filtering for network-wide blocking</li>
          <li>Reserve software filtering only for critical devices</li>
          <li>Use built-in device controls (Screen Time, Family Link) instead of 3rd-party apps</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Advanced Optimizations</h2>

      <Accordion title="Enable DNS over TLS (DoT) for Speed">
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Paradoxically, encrypted DNS can be faster because it prevents ISP interference:
        </p>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Check if your router supports DoT (advanced routers only)</li>
          <li>Configure with your filtering provider's DoT address</li>
          <li>
            Example - CleanBrowsing DoT: <code
              class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono"
              >family-filter-dns.cleanbrowsing.org</code
            >
          </li>
          <li>Can reduce latency by 5-15ms if ISP was interfering</li>
        </ol>
        <Alert type="warning">
          Not all routers support this. Don't use DoH (DNS over HTTPS) as it bypasses filtering.
        </Alert>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="Use Local DNS Resolver (Pi-hole)">
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Advanced users can run a local DNS server that caches aggressively:
        </p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Pi-hole:</strong> Runs on Raspberry Pi ($35), caches all DNS locally</li>
          <li>First lookup: normal speed</li>
          <li>Subsequent lookups: &lt;1ms (instant)</li>
          <li>Bonus: Blocks ads network-wide</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Pi-hole can forward to filtering DNS providers for content blocking. See <a
            href="/guides/firewall"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-400 dark:hover:text-blue-300 underline"
            >advanced filtering guide</a
          >.
        </p>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="Configure Quality of Service (QoS)">
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Prioritize important traffic over background tasks:
        </p>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Router admin ‚Üí QoS or Traffic Management</li>
          <li>Enable QoS</li>
          <li>Prioritize: VoIP calls, video calls, gaming</li>
          <li>Deprioritize: Downloads, updates, file transfers</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          This won't fix slow speeds, but makes important tasks feel faster.
        </p>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="Separate WiFi Networks by Speed">
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Older devices on WiFi 4 (802.11n) slow down the entire network:
        </p>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 list-decimal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Create two WiFi networks: one 5GHz only, one 2.4GHz</li>
          <li>Put fast devices on 5GHz network</li>
          <li>Put IoT/old devices on 2.4GHz network</li>
          <li>Apply filtering DNS to both</li>
        </ol>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="Monitor Bandwidth Hogs">
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Identify which devices/apps consume most bandwidth:
        </p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Router admin may show per-device usage</li>
          <li>Use GlassWire (Windows) or Little Snitch (Mac) on computers</li>
          <li>Common culprits: Steam downloads, iCloud backup, Windows updates</li>
          <li>Schedule heavy downloads for off-peak hours</li>
        </ul>
      </Accordion>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">When It's Not Fixable</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Sometimes slowdowns have no solution except upgrading:
      </p>

      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Your Internet Plan Is Too Slow</h4>
      <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
        <li>Modern households need 100+ Mbps for 4+ people</li>
        <li>Streaming 4K needs 25 Mbps per stream</li>
        <li>Video calls need 5-10 Mbps upload</li>
        <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Upgrade internet plan with ISP</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">You Have Too Many Devices</h4>
      <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
        <li>Budget routers handle 10-15 devices maximum</li>
        <li>Each smart home device adds load</li>
        <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Upgrade to business-grade router or mesh system</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-6 mb-3">Your House Is Too Large</h4>
      <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 list-disc text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-2">
        <li>Single router struggles beyond 2,000 sq ft</li>
        <li>Weak WiFi signal = slow speeds</li>
        <li><strong>Solution:</strong> Mesh WiFi system (Eero, Google WiFi, Orbi)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Prevention Checklist</h2>
      <ul class="list-none ml-0 space-y-2">
        <li
          class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold"
        >
          Use fastest filtering DNS provider for your location (test with ping)
        </li>
        <li
          class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold"
        >
          Keep router firmware updated
        </li>
        <li
          class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold"
        >
          Reboot router monthly (set calendar reminder)
        </li>
        <li
          class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold"
        >
          Don't run multiple security/filtering apps on same device
        </li>
        <li
          class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold"
        >
          Use Ethernet for desktop computers and gaming consoles
        </li>
        <li
          class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold"
        >
          Position router centrally, elevated, away from interference
        </li>
        <li
          class="pl-6 relative text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed before:content-['‚úì'] before:absolute before:left-0 before:text-green-600 dark:before:text-green-400 before:font-bold"
        >
          Upgrade router every 3-4 years
        </li>
      </ul>
